[I] Gnome Partition Editor

[T] GParted is a free partition editor for graphically managing your disk
[T] partitions, for creating, destroying, resizing, checking and copying
[T] partitions, and the file systems on them. This is useful for creating space
[T] for new operating systems, reorganizing disk usage, copying data residing
[T] on hard disks and mirroring one partition with another (disk imaging).

[U] https://gparted.sourceforge.net

[A] Bart Hakvoort <gparted@users.sourceforge.net>
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

